SIMPLE: womanhood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Womanhood
<hw>Wom"an*hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being a woman; the distinguishing character or qualities of a
woman, or of womankind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unspotted faith, and comely <qex>womanhood</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Perhaps the smile and the tender tone⟦br⟧
Came out of her pitying <qex>womanhood</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Women, collectively; womankind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>womanise</ent>⟦br⟧
